The ANC caucus in Johannesburg says it’s disappointed in the Council Speaker for not allowing a secret ballot. eNCA's Govan Whittles reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg's first council meeting for the year has been postponed to Tuesday. This after chaos erupted over the ballot. READ: First Joburg council sitting of 2022 delayed by protests The chaos disrupted the election of chairpersons of oversight committees. The multi-party coalition led by the DA wanted an open ballot. But, the minority coalition was opposed to this.